# Busibox SSO Authentication

## Context
- Uses Busibox authz service for authentication
- RS256 JWT tokens validated via JWKS
- Zero Trust token exchange pattern

## Token Flow

```
1. User clicks app in Busibox Portal
2. Busibox Portal exchanges session JWT for app-scoped token via authz
3. authz verifies user has app access via RBAC bindings
4. authz issues RS256 token with app_id claim and user's roles
5. App validates token via authz JWKS endpoint
```

## Requirements

### Auth Middleware Usage

```typescript
import { requireAuthWithTokenExchange } from '@/lib/auth-middleware';

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const auth = await requireAuthWithTokenExchange(request);
  if (auth instanceof NextResponse) return auth;

  // auth.ssoToken - original session JWT
  // auth.apiToken - exchanged API token for backend calls
  // auth.isTestUser - true if using TEST_SESSION_JWT
}
```

### Optional Auth

```typescript
import { optionalAuth } from '@/lib/auth-middleware';

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const auth = await optionalAuth(request);
  
  if (auth) {
    // Authenticated request
  } else {
    // Anonymous request
  }
}
```

### SSO Validation

```typescript
import { validateSSOToken } from '@/lib/sso';

const result = await validateSSOToken(token);
if (result.valid) {
  // result.userId, result.roles, result.scopes
} else {
  // result.error
}
```

### Role Checking

```typescript
import { hasRole, isAdmin } from '@/lib/sso';

if (isAdmin(session)) {
  // Admin-only logic
}

if (hasRole(session, 'Editor')) {
  // Editor logic
}
```

## Environment Variables

```bash
AUTHZ_BASE_URL=http://authz:8010
APP_NAME=My App  # Token audience
```

<critical>
- NEVER expose tokens in client-side code
- ALWAYS validate tokens server-side
- NEVER skip authentication for data routes
</critical>
